title: Warriors blank Red Raiders
text: Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 10:08 PM By Cape Cod Times Posted Oct. 12, 2015 at 10:08 PM » Social News Cape Cod Times sports@capecodonline.com NORTH EASTHAM - Sophomore Emily McGrath knocked home a pair of goals and senior Sarah Hemmings made it stand as the Nauset Warriors shutout the Barnstable Red Raiders, 2-0, on Monday evening. McGrath gave Hemmings all the offense she would need, finishing off a penalty kick in the first half as Nauset (4-5-2) took a 1-0 lead to the break. McGrath added an insurance goal in the second half, off an assist from senior Caley Fry. Sophomore Isabel Pellegrini and senior Dawn Johnson were key in the midfield for the Warriors while Hailey Adams was strong in the midfield for Barnstable (1-7-1). The Red Raiders also got strong play on defense from Emma Field and Jordan Cooke. Avon 2, Upper Cape 1: Amber DiBona had the Rams goal in a loss to the Panthers in Avon. Danielle Mueller kept Upper Cape (4-7-1) in the match with nine saves, while the Rams also got strong play from Kaelyn Hooper and Alexis Desrosiers. Monomoy 6, Randolph 0: Five different players found the back of the net for the Sharks in a win over the Blue Devils in Randolph. Tara Barry, Ashley Benson, Emily Sanders, Abby Wallace and Kelsey Olson all scored in the victory for Monomoy (2-6). The Sharks’ sixth goal came on a Randolph own goal. Francesca Barr added a pair of assists while Benson also added an assist. The Sharks host Carver on Wednesday. By Cape Cod Times
